
# =============================================================================
# .gitignore — peer-factory-evatec-2026-q2
# Strategy: Track all project knowledge. Ignore only generated, licensed,
# temporary, and machine-specific files.
# =============================================================================


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Node.js / Playwright — generated, not project knowledge
# Restore with: npm ci && npx playwright install
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
node_modules/
/test-results/
/playwright-report/
/blob-report/
/playwright/.cache/
/playwright/.auth/


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Python cache — generated bytecode, not project knowledge
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# OS and editor noise — machine-specific, not project knowledge
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo
*~


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Temporary and scratch files — not project knowledge
# Risk: files like .tmp-qa-analysis.ps1 at repo root may contain work-in-progress.
# Recommendation: move to a named folder (e.g. scratch/) or commit with intent.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.tmp
*.bak
*.log
*.csv
.tmp-*


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Licensed reference material — SEMI PDF standards are third-party IP.
# Must not be redistributed via source control.
# Recommendation: store locally or in a licensed shared drive.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
*.pdf


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Personal VS Code workspace files — machine-specific, not team knowledge.
# Exception: .vscode/project.instructions.md is team knowledge and is unignored below.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.vscode/settings.json
.vscode/launch.json
.vscode/tasks.json
.vscode/*.prompt.md
.vscode/*.agent.md


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Personal Copilot data — local cache, not project knowledge
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
.copilot/


# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Excel files — TRACKED as source artifacts.
# Excel workbooks are primary quality gates in this project.
# WARNING: The previous rule *.xlsx was REMOVED. Excel files should be committed.
# If an Excel file must be excluded, add an explicit path-specific rule below.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# (no Excel ignore rules — all .xlsx/.xls files are tracked intentionally)


# =============================================================================
# EXPLICIT UNIGNORES — override any pattern above that would wrongly exclude
# project knowledge artifacts
# =============================================================================

# Team-shared Copilot instructions — essential project knowledge
!.github/copilot-instructions.md
!.github/copilot-workspace-standards.instructions.md
!.github/copilot-qa-audit.instructions.md
!.github/copilot-dotnet.instructions.md

# Copilot prompts — project knowledge, reusable workflows, onboarding aids
# Previously ignored; restored to tracking per audit review.
!.github/prompts/
!.github/prompts/**

# VS Code shared project instructions
!.vscode/project.instructions.md
